          "text" : "Conditions for always positive or always negative",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Discriminant",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Discriminant",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Discriminants are based on the quadratic formula. Basically, if the square root part of the quadratic formula:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Has a positive value: the quadratic function has two real roots",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Has a zero value: the quadratic function has one real root",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Has a negative value: the quadratic function has no real roots, and is either always positive or always negative",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The discriminant is defined as:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "\\Delta = b^2 - 4ac"
          ],
          "syntax" : "math",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Conditions",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Conditions",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "For a quadratic function to be always positive, the discriminant must be less than zero and the coefficient of the x^2 term must be positive:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "\\Delta < 0",
            "a > 0"
          ],
          "syntax" : "math",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "For a quadratic function to be always negative, the discriminant must be less than zero and the coefficient of the x^2 term must be negative:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "\\Delta < 0",
            "a < 0"
          ],
          "syntax" : "math",
          "type" : "codeListing"
